<F P=100> CANADA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government To Suspend Commercial Flights to Haiti </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government To Suspend Commercial Flights to Haiti </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1006190294 Mexico City NOTIMEX in Spanish 1744 GMT 10 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1006190294 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City NOTIMEX </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Montreal, 10 Jun (NOTIMEX) -- The Canadian 
Government will suspend commercial flights to Haiti beginning on 
25 June, Andre Ouellet, the Canadian minister of foreign 
affairs, has announced. 
  He added that the decision to suspend commercial flights to 
Haiti was made to comply with a resolution that the OAS adopted 
last week calling for increased pressure on the coupist Haitian 
Government. Ouellet said that he plans to discuss with the 
cabinet the adoption of "additional measures," which according 
to official sources, "will affect the financial transactions" 
between the two countries. 
  The United States today announced the suspension of flights 
to Haiti, beginning on 25 June. 
  The Canadian Foreign Affairs Ministry also recommended to 
its 
citizens in that country to "leave the island while possible 
through regular flights." 

</TEXT>

