<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Good Starting Position' for October </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Good Starting Position' for October </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1306131994 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1235 GMT 13 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1306131994 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DDP/ADN) -- Chancellor Helmut Kohl, CDU 
[Christian Democratic Union] chairman, has described the showing 
of the CDU and CSU [Christian Social Union] in the European 
election as a "very good starting position" for the forthcoming 
state parliament elections and for the Bundestag election in 
October. Following meetings of the CDU presidium and executive, 
Kohl said in Bonn this afternoon that the CDU and CSU have 
"reached an important stage." However, there are no grounds for 
sounding an all-clear. In the coming weeks and months, the CDU 
and CSU will have to fight for every vote, he stated. Kohl is 
also confident that the Free Democratic Party will again enter 
the new Bundestag. 

</TEXT>

