<H3> <TI>   Kinkel Asserts No Change in FDP Course </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kinkel Asserts No Change in FDP Course </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1306125894 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1154 GMT 13 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1306125894 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DDP/ADN) -- FDP [Free Democratic Party] 
Chairman Klaus Kinkel has reaffirmed that his party will not 
change its course for the Bundestag elections despite its result 
in the European elections. "We are determined to continue our 
coalition with the CDU/CSU [Christian Democratic Union/Christian 
Social Union]," Kinkel stressed at noon today after committee 
meetings of the Liberals in Bonn. He assumed that the FDP would 
"double" its Sunday [12 June] result at the Bundestag elections 
and that the coalition with the CDU/CSU could continue after 16 
October. The presidium and the executive had agreed that 
blaming individuals within the FDP would not help anybody. The 
party now had to concentrate on clarifying its policies to the 
people. 

</TEXT>

