<H3> <TI>   Ministry Outraged by News of Rwandan Massacre </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ministry Outraged by News of Rwandan Massacre </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1106221794 Paris France-Inter Radio Network in French 2100 
GMT 11 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1106221794 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris France-Inter Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The French Foreign Ministry has expressed its 
outrage at the announcement of another massacre in Rwanda -- 170 
people, including many children, were kidnapped and killed in 
Kigali. 
  It is urgent that, during the OAU summit in Tunis, the 
countries in the area do their utmost in order to persuade the 
belligerents in Rwanda to put an immediate end to the fighting, 
the Foreign Ministry said. It has also called on the reinforced 
UN mission to be deployed as soon as possible in order to 
intervene between the two sides. 

</TEXT>

