<H3> <TI>   PP `Winner' in European Parliament Elections </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PP `Winner' in European Parliament Elections </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1306002094 Madrid RNE-1 Radio Network in Spanish 0000 GMT 
13 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1306002094 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid RNE-1 Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] The People's Party [PP] has been named the winner 
in elections held on Sunday [12 June] in Spain to the European 
Parliament. It received 40.2 percent of the votes cast and 28 
seats. The Spanish Workers Socialist Party received 30.62 
percent of the vote and 22 seats. United Left received 13.5 
percent of the vote and nine seats, while Convergence and Union 
will have three seats and the Nationalist Coalition will have 
two seats. [passage omitted] 

