  [Excerpt] There has been no official reaction to the report 
carried by REUTER that President Glavkos Kliridhis expressed the 
intention to resign if the UN Security Council decides to 
continue talks on the confidence-building measures. 
  The government spokesman avoided making any comment and said 
that the letters that the president has sent to President 
Clinton and British Prime Minister John Major are confidential. 
REUTER reported that President Kliridhis' threat to resign is 
outlined in these letters. [passage omitted] 

