<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Turkish Cypriots Reportedly Murdered by Secret Services </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Turkish Cypriots Reportedly Murdered by Secret Services </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1206071894 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1900 GMT 11 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1206071894 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] According to updated information acquired by the 
security authorities, it appears that the murder of the two 
Turkish Cypriots in Stavrokonos village is the work of the 
Turkish Secret Services. 
  Based on this information, it appears that the crime was 
carried out by people who were acting on the orders of the 
Turkish Secret Services. One of the victims, (Ozker Tufansu), 
was a major witness for the Republic of Cyprus to overturn 
claims by Turkish Cypriot leader Rauf Denktas' regime that 22 
Turkish Cypriots who were living in the free areas had been 
brutally mistreated by the police. Tufansu, who was in the free 
areas, fled to the occupied areas but later returned. Ten days 
before his assassination, he revealed Turkish activities to the 
police. A few days ago, two deserters who were soldiers at the 
Attila line [the buffer zone] came to the free areas because 
they said they could not tolerate the occupation regime's 
suppression. 
  Approximately 400 Turkish Cypriots live in the free areas 
today and 180 of them are deserters. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

