<F P=100> SWITZERLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Voters: `No' to UN Peacekeeping Participation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Voters: `No' to UN Peacekeeping Participation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1206143694 Paris AFP in English 1424 GMT 12 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1206143694 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bern, June 12 (AFP) -- Swiss voters decided Sunday 
[12 June] in a referendum against participating in any UN 
peacekeeping operations, local radio and news agency reports 
said. 
  The French-speaking Swiss radio station said voting results 
from a majority of cantons showed that more than 60 percent of 
voters had said no to a proposal of contributing 600 Swiss 
soldiers to the UN. 

</TEXT>

