<H3> <TI>   Denies Health Rumors </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Denies Health Rumors </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1206062694 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 0430 GMT 12 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1206062694 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Andreas Papandreou has described as 
wretched and shameful the rumors that circulated a few hours 
before the beginning of the European Parliament elections. 
According to the rumors, he is allegedly facing a health 
problem. 
  Mr. Papandreou also pointed out that such rumors are trotted 
out before every election showdown and stressed that those who 
start these rumors should be ashamed. 

</TEXT>

