<F P=100> GREECE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Explosions Rock Athens, Group Claims Responsibility </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Explosions Rock Athens, Group Claims Responsibility </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1106063094 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 0400 GMT 11 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1106063094 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] There was a barrage of explosions last night in the 
center of Athens. Specifically, within 15 minutes at around 
midnight homemade explosive devices went off in a school bus 
from the Kostas Yitonas educational institute at the 
intersection of Skiros and Evelpidhes Streets in Kipseli [Athens 
suburb], at a refreshment shop on Andrianos Street in Plaka 
[Athens district], and outside the Thivai textile mill on 
Kapnitareas Street. 
  A very strong explosion also took place at 0230 today at the 
intersection of Vasilissis Sofias and (Iridhanos) Streets, 
destroying a small, white truck with the registration No. YZ8660. 
  The Antiauthority Battle [Andiexousiastiki Pali] 
organization 
made a telephone call to a private radio station claiming 
responsibility only for the first explosion. 

</TEXT>

