<F P=100> Turkey </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Puts Provincial Security Forces on Alert </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Puts Provincial Security Forces on Alert </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0906203194 Istanbul HURRIYET in Turkish 5 Jun 94 p 18 </F>
<F P=103> NC0906203194 </F>
<F P=104>  Istanbul HURRIYET </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Sezai Sengun: "Joint Action by PKK and ASALA" -- </F>
place names as published] 
  [Text] Ankara--Acting on information that the Workers Party 
of Kurdistan [PKK] terrorists in Armenia are preparing to 
infiltrate into Turkey, officials have placed the security 
forces in Kars, Ardahan, and Igdir Provinces on a state of 
alert. Meanwhile, the 3d Army units have intensified Turkey's 
security measures along the Armenian border. 
  According to an intelligence report submitted to the 
National 
Security Council, the PKK terrorists and the ASALA [Armenian 
Secret Army for the Liberation of Armenia] militants are 
cooperating in carrying out joint activities against Turkey. 
The report outlined the locations of the PKK camps in Armenia 
as follows: 
  1. Mirak, Elegiz, Reya Taze, Shengavit, Derik, Suphan, 
Cumusvan, Amri Taze, and Senger in Aragaz District. 
  2. Sorik, Hako, Tellik, and Baysiz in Talin District. 
  3. Ferik in Echmiadzin District. 
  4. Samirin in Ashtarak District. 
  The report said the PKK terrorists train in those villages 
and organize armed exercises from time to time. It also said 
that they are strongly supported by the local people. The 
report stressed: "It is believed that the PKK terrorists and 
ASALA members will organize joint attacks against Turkey. The 
Kars, Ardahan, and Igdir Provinces, which have a common border 
with Armenia, are cautioned to take the necessary measures and 
maintain a state of vigilance." 
  The report said that PKK leader Abdullah Ocalan is 
personally 
maintaining his organization's relations with Armenia and that 
the Armenian officials have been informed of and support the PKK 
activities. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

