  [Text] State of Emergency Governor Unal Erkan has stated 
that 1,700 terrorists have been killed and 2,000 captured in 
operations conducted by the security forces in the last five 
months. 
  Addressing the inauguration ceremony of the security 
directorate building in Adiyaman's Celikkan District, Erkan said 
that 4,700 abettors also have been captured during the same 
period. According to information given by Erkan 300 terrorists, 
140 of them leaders, have surrendered to the security forces 
during that time. Some 2,000 rifles, 5,000 rounds of 
ammunition, 2,000 rockets, 1,950 hand grenades and 300 tonnes of 
foodstuff also have been seized. [passage indistinct]. 

