<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    More Statistics </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1206151394 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1410 GMT 12 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA1206151394 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Diyarbakir, June 12 (A.A.) -- Thirty-seven 
terrorists from the separatist terrorist organization were 
killed and nine others surrendered to security forces in 
southeastern provinces, it was reported on Sunday [12 June]. 
  Emergency Regional Governor's Office told AA [ANATOLIA] that 
22 terrorists were killed in Eylul Mountain in Kulp township in 
Diyarbakir Province, seven were killed in Kuyulu village in 
Derik township in Mardin Province, six terrorists were killed in 
Balkaya region in Semdinli township in Hakkari Province and two 
others were killed in Dogantepe region in Eruh township in Siirt 
Province. 
  Meanwhile, nine terrorists surrendered to security force in 
Diyarbakir, Adiyaman, Bingol, Hakkari, Siirt and Tunceli 
Provinces. 

</TEXT>

