<H3> <TI>   Anti-Iran Activists Caught; Asylum Denied </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Anti-Iran Activists Caught; Asylum Denied </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1106160994 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1500 GMT 11 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA1106160994 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, June 11 (AA) -- Sixteen members from an 
outlawed organization fighting against the regime in Iran were 
captured in Ankara, it was reported on Saturday [11 June]. 
  AA reporter learned that the members of `People's 
Mujaheddins' [Mojahedin-e Khalq] were captured after operations 
carried out in three different safe-houses in the city, 
following tip-offs. 
  Their request for political asylum was refused by the 
Interior Ministry and they were sent to a camp in southeastern 
Silopi town to be later expelled. 
  A high-level official said that Turkey will not allow any 
organization working against its neighbours within its 
territories, adding likewise the terrorist PKK [Workers Party of 
Kurdistan] organization should not be allowed to work in Iran. 
  "This latest operation is a show of our good-will," he 
added. 

</TEXT>

