<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russian Troops Hold Farewell Ceremony in Wuensdorf </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russian Troops Hold Farewell Ceremony in Wuensdorf </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1106091994 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 0832 GMT 11 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1106091994 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Wuensdorf (DDP/ADN) -- The supreme command of 
the Western Group of Russian Troops (WGT) in Wuensdorf, 
Brandenburg, officially bade farewell to Germany with a troop 
parade today. After the parade, which included military 
hardware and around 1,000 soldiers, WGT Commander in Chief 
Colonel General Matvey Burlakov and Prime Minister of 
Brandenburg Manfred Stolpe spoke in favor of completing the 
final phase of troop withdrawal in a dignified way and of 
cultivating friendly contacts in future. 
  Stolpe assured the returnees further support in providing 
housing in Russia and training for civilian jobs. He pointed 
out that the Western Group had so far carried out the return of 
troops successfully and without major incidents. [passage 
omitted] 
  The official date for the final withdrawal of the Russian 
troops from Germany is 31 August. 

</TEXT>

