<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Preliminary' Results of European Elections </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Preliminary' Results of European Elections </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1306105994 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 0937 GMT 13 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1306105994 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DDP/ADN) -- The federal returning officer 
announced the preliminary final results of the European 
elections in Bonn this morning. The CDU [Christian Democratic 
Union] and CSU [Christian Social Union] are the strongest forces 
in Germany, with 38.8 percent between them. The SPD [Social 
Democratic Party] suffered losses and reached only 32.2 percent. 
At 4.1 percent, the FDP [Free Democratic Party] failed to 
overcome the 5-percent hurdle. On the other hand, Alliance 
90/Greens improved their vote to 10.1 percent. The PDS [Party 
of Democratic Socialism], the successor party to the SED, 
received 4.7 percent and the extreme right-wing Republicans got 
3.9 percent. The turnout was 60.1 percent. 

</TEXT>

