<H3> <TI>   Iranian Interior Minister Arrives on Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Iranian Interior Minister Arrives on Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1306113294 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1000 
GMT 13 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1306113294 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] Iranian Interior Minister 'Ali Mohammad 
Besharati-Jahromi arrived in Ankara on an official visit today. 
He was received at Esenboga Airport by Interior Minister Nahit 
Mentese. In a statement at the airport, Mentese said that 
Turkey and Iran, which are linked by common values, unity of 
faith, and deep cultural ties, are two friendly, neighboring 
countries with special relations. Mentese stressed that the 
Turkish-Iranian border has been a line of peace for many 
centuries. 
  [Begin Mentese recording] As two neighboring countries, 
Turkey and Iran have common fields of information on which they 
must exchange views, especially in the security area. It is 
also a known fact that certain developments which take place in 
one country affects the other as well. [end recording] 
  In his statement, the Iranian interior minister declared 
that 
the security issue as well as military, political, and 
interparliamentary matters will be discussed during the talks in 
Turkey. Besharati noted: It is my impression that this is the 
first time that the friendly relations between Iran and Turkey 
have reached such a high level. 
  The two ministers then left Esenboga for Izmir, where 
Besharati will be received by President Suleyman Demirel before 
returning to Ankara. 

</TEXT>

