<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kohl, Mitterrand To Urge Chernobyl Closure at Corfu </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kohl, Mitterrand To Urge Chernobyl Closure at Corfu </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1306120794 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1100 GMT 13 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1306120794 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DDP/ADN) -- Chancellor Helmut Kohl and French 
President Francois Mitterrand have lent emphasis to their 
initiative for a speedy closure of the Ukrainian nuclear power 
station Chernobyl. In a letter to the heads of state and 
government of the European Union (EU) and the G-7 countries, as 
well as to European Commission President Jacques Delors, the two 
leaders said that another accident in Chernobyl would have 
far-reaching consequences for the population, the whole human 
race, and the international energy situation. The initiative 
was announced by Kohl and Mitterrand at the French-German summit 
in Mulhouse [at the end of May]. 
  According to government spokesman Dieter Vogel, Kohl and 
Mitterrand expressed their conviction that the topic will be a 
"central issue" of the talks at the EU summit in Corfu at the 
end of June and at the G-7 summit in Naples in mid-July. A plan 
of action for the closure of Chernobyl is to be decided on in 
Naples. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

