<H3> <TI>   Slovene Delegation Attends WEU Meeting in Paris </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Slovene Delegation Attends WEU Meeting in Paris </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1306150894 Ljubljana Radio Slovenia Network in Slovene 
1330 GMT 13 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1306150894 </F>
<F P=104>  Ljubljana Radio Slovenia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Slovene </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The first part of this year's meeting of the 
Western European Union [WEU] opened in Paris today. A Slovene 
parliamentary delegation has also been invited to attend the 
meeting as an observer. Our delegation consists of Borut Pahor, 
head of the Slovene delegation to the European Council 
Parliamentary Conference [as heard], and Jozef Kupse, chairman 
of the Parliamentary Committee for Defense. What is above all 
important for Slovenia, is to successfully present in Paris our 
country's interest in acquiring the status of WEU associate 
member. 

</TEXT>

