<H3> <TI>   Iran Denies Weekly's Claim of Links With ETA </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Iran Denies Weekly's Claim of Links With ETA </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1306200294 Tehran IRNA in English 1939 GMT 13 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1306200294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Madrid, June 13, IRNA -- The Iranian Embassy here 
today rejected as "baseless and utterly false" a report in the 
latest issue of the weekly TIEMPO alleging secret links between 
Iranians and the Basque separatist group ETA (Euzkadi Ta 
Azcatasuma [Basque Fatherland and Liberty]). 
  The statement said "Iranian officials believe that the 
objective behind the groundless article is to create tension in 
the friendly relations between Islamic Iran and Spain." 
  ETA which means `Basque Homeland and Liberty' was founded in 
1959 and is regarded as an `illegal terrorist' organization by 
the Spanish Government. 
  The Basques are an ethnic minority inhabiting the western 
Pyrenees mountains in northern Spain on the Bay of Biscay. 

</TEXT>

