<F P=100> ITALY &amp; VATICAN CITY </F>
<H3> <TI>   PDS Leader Ochetto Resigns After European Elections </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PDS Leader Ochetto Resigns After European Elections </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1306141094 Paris AFP in English 1355 GMT 13 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1306141094 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Rome, June 13 (AFP) -- Reformed communist (PDS) 
[Democratic Party of the Left] party chief Achille Occhetto 
resigned, the PDS press department announced Monday [13 June]. 
  The PDS garnered 19.1 percent of the votes in Sunday's 
European Parliament elections against 20.4 percent in the March 
general elections in Italy. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

