<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   EU Ministers: Turkish Cypriots Cause Talks To Fail </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    EU Ministers: Turkish Cypriots Cause Talks To Fail </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1406115394 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1030 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1406115394 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A short time ago, a Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation 
correspondent reported from Luxembourg that the European Union 
[EU] Council of Foreign Ministers has approved a joint statement 
on the Cyprus issue. In their statement the 12 ministers blame 
the Turkish Cypriot side for the failure of the talks and plan 
to discuss the Cyprus issue at the EU summit in Corfu. 
  According to our correspondent, during the second day of its 
session the council asked Serge Abou, the EU observer at the 
Cyprus talks, to present a new report at the EU summit. The 
council has also approved the Cyprus-EU Fourth Financial 
Protocol, which amounts to ECU74 million. 

</TEXT>

