<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kliridhis Threatens To Resign `If Necessary' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kliridhis Threatens To Resign `If Necessary' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1406100394 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 0900 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1406100394 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President Glavkos Kliridhis today said he has made 
it clear that he will resign from his post, if necessary, to 
give the people the opportunity to decide whether they want 
further discussion on the confidence-building measures, or 
whether they prefer to insist on effective alternative 
procedures before negotiations on the substance of the issue 
that will open the way for a solution are held. 
  He added: If the UN Security Council follows this procedure, 
we would be ready to help the secretary general find a just and 
viable solution to the Cyprus problem. The president said he 
has made it clear that he remains committed to the 21 March UN 
document on implementing the confidence-building measures that 
was prepared by the UN secretary general's representatives, and 
in his report Butrus-Ghali described it as a fair and balanced 
document. 
  The president made this statement this morning during an 
address at a ceremony to receive the credentials of the new 
Jordanian ambassador to Cyprus. 

</TEXT>

