<F P=100> GREECE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ministry on Terms for Lifting FYROM Embargo </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ministry on Terms for Lifting FYROM Embargo </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1306180294 Athens ET-1 Television Network in 1500 GMT 13 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1306180294 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens ET-1 Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  1500 </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] New deliberations on the issue of Skopje [The Former 
Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia--FYROM] will begin in New York 
with Cyrus Vance and Greek Foreign Minister Karolos Papoulias 
who will go there tomorrow. Vance will also meet with Skopjean 
Foreign Minister Stevo Crvenkovski. 
  [Begin Foreign Ministry spokesman Konstandinos Bikas 
recording] Our position on the issue of Skopje's name is firm. 
We will not recognize a state that has the term `Macedonia' in 
its name. Furthermore, a condition for the lifting of the 
embargo is a change of Skopje's flag, either by amending the 
constitution, or having Skopje submit a binding peaceful 
declaration to the United Nations. It should confirm at the 
first opportunity that it will take the necessary steps in 
parliament to change the relevant articles of its constitution. 
[end recording] 

</TEXT>

