<H3> <TI>   Court Rules To Stop Government Decree Powers </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Court Rules To Stop Government Decree Powers </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1006195494 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1700 
GMT 10 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1006195494 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report] </F>
  [Text] The Constitutional Court has ruled to stop the 
implementation of the law allowing the government to issue 
law-decrees to make changes in the state organization and 
personnel regulations. 
  The Motherland Party applied to the Constitutional Court 
asking it to stop the implementation of the law until the case 
for its cancellation is concluded. The Constitutional Court 
discussed the application today and with a majority of votes, 
ruled to stop the implementation of the law to prevent 
situations and losses that might be impossible or difficult to 
recover. 

</TEXT>

