<H3> <TI>   Opposition Leader Yilmaz Leaves for U.S. </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Opposition Leader Yilmaz Leaves for U.S. </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1306114894 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1000 
GMT 13 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1306114894 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] Motherland Party leader Mesut Yilmaz left for the 
United States today to attend the World Forum to be held in 
Denver. In a predeparture statement at Istanbul's Ataturk 
Airport, Yilmaz said many distinguished statesmen will attend 
the meeting, to be held under the chairmanship of former U.S. 
President Gerald Ford. International security policies and 
topics concerning the world economy will be discussed at the 
meeting, Yilmaz reported. He added that possible global 
developments in the 2000's will also be on the agenda. 
  Yilmaz explained that he will then proceed to Washington, 
where he will meet with U.S. Administration and Congressional 
officials. He stated: I will have the opportunity to convey 
our views on various issues to U.S. officials, particularly at 
this time when we are experiencing some tension in Turkish-U.S. 
relations. 
  In reply to a question on whether he will discuss the 
extension of the Poised Hammer mandate with U.S. officials, 
Yilmaz said: 
  [Begin Yilmaz recording] The question of whether the Poised 
Hammer mandate will be extended depends on the decision of the 
Turkish Grand National Assembly. The importance the U.S. 
Administration attaches to this issue is evident, and if U.S. 
officials raise the subject, I will convey our views to them. 
[end recording] 
  Yilmaz remarked that on 20 June, he will hold a news 
conference on his contacts in the United States, and he will 
return to Turkey the following day. 

</TEXT>

