<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-43204 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drweu114_q_94009" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-WEU-94-114 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  13 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kurdish Leaders Meet in Silopi; Cetin Comments </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kurdish Leaders Meet in Silopi; Cetin Comments </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1306185194 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1700 
GMT 13 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1306185194 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] In an effort to end the ongoing clashes in northern 
Iraq, Northern Iraqi Kurdish leaders Mas'ud Barzani and Jalal 
Talabani met in Sirnak's Silopi District. The Gendarmerie 
General Commander General Aydin Ilter attended the meeting. 
  Foreign Minister Hikmet Cetin answered reporters' questions 
on the issue after leaving the Council of Ministers meeting in 
Ankara. Cetin stated that there was an unstable atmosphere in 
northern Iraq and added that the clashes between rival Kurdish 
groups exacerbated the already unstable situation. Cetin said 
that the aim of the meeting in Silopi was to end this unstable 
situation and stop the bloodshed. 
  Explaining that the issue of fighting terrorism in northern 
Iraq will be assessed during the meetings, Cetin added: Our 
gendarmerie general commander has frequently conducted meetings 
of this kind. After a lengthy interval, such a meeting is again 
taking place. 
  In answer to a question, Cetin said that officials from the 
foreign ministry and the interior ministry are participating in 
the meetings in addition to the gendarmerie general commander. 

</TEXT>

