  [Text] Quite understandably, Prime Minister Silvio 
Berlusconi is very happy both at the strengthening of the 
government coalition and at his personal success: he was on top 
of his party's lists in all five Italian constituencies. Let us 
listen now to the prime minister's first reaction after the 
first projections last night. He was speaking on the phone to 
RAI Uno. 
  [Begin Berlusconi recording] I think the victory will 
encourage all cabinet members to continue in the same direction 
in which we started. As far as I am concerned, I must say that 
it will encourage me to try as hard as I can and to work with 
