with the approval of so many citizens. 
  As for the situation in the Senate, I hope the opposition 
will learn from what happened and that they will want to be in 
opposition in a positive way. The opposition is comprised of 
several groups today -- I clearly mean the Italian Popular Party 
-- which should think about these results and about their 
behavior. This would lead them, I believe, to get more in touch 
with their electorate, that is, people who want to remain among 
the moderates and want to support the government. [end 
recording] 

