<F P=104>  Athens ET-1 Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The day after the elections is more important for 
the political parties. The results, which contradicted all 
preelection polls, have political party officials thinking 
seriously. Despite the euphoria of the smaller parties whose 
power was increased significantly, their officials are also 
examining the results seriously. 
  The final results were announced just a short while ago: 
PASOK [Panhellenic Socialist Movement] received 37.64 percent 
of the vote and 10 seats; New Democracy received 32.66 percent 
and nine seats; Political Spring received 8.65 percent and two 
seats; KKE [Greek Communist Party] received 6.29 percent and two 
seats; and the Coalition of the Left and Progress received 6.25 
percent and two seats. DIANA [Democratic Renewal], which 
received 2.79 percent of the vote, did not manage to elect a 
deputy to the European Parliament. 

</TEXT>

