<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report signed "a.z.": "NATO Officer as Wire-Puller in </F>
Cocaine Scene"] 
  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] Dragan B. has been exposed as 
a cocaine dealer. He repeatedly smuggled cocaine from Belgium 
and Colombia to Austria. During his last coup he was caught in 
Dusseldorf by the German police, which had been alerted by the 
Austrians. He had 4 kg of cocaine on him with a street value of 
7.5 million schillings. One kilogram of cocaine from previous 
deliveries was found in the possession of eight gang members, 
among whom it had been distributed. 
  In Belgium, the Vienna police has now established the 
identity of a high-ranking Belgian NATO officer who had supplied 
the cocaine. The Belgian authorities, however, have so far 
ignored the Austrian investigations: Not only has the arrest 
warrant not been executed, and the suspect, who has been 
incriminated by several witnesses, has not only not been 
extradited, the Belgians have not even arrested the man. "This 
man is somehow untouchable," police sources said. 
  Eight individuals have been arrested, while complaints 
against another 25 have been filed. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

