<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   RAF Supporters Reportedly Active in Duesseldorf Area </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    RAF Supporters Reportedly Active in Duesseldorf Area </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1406170694 Munich FOCUS in German 13 Jun 94 p 13 </F>
<F P=103> AU1406170694 </F>
<F P=104>  Munich FOCUS </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Terrorist Friends on the Rhine"] </F>
  [Text] A militant support group of the terrorist Red Army 
Faction (RAF) is active in the greater Duesseldorf area. 
Experts from the Office for the Protection of the Constitution 
are proceeding on this assumption after analyzing the bomb 
attack on the Christian Democratic Union [CDU] district office 
in Duesseldorf on 5 June and the letter claiming responsibility 
for it. 
  Among the accomplices of the circle of the RAF auxiliary 
troop are reportedly people who reported on the territory around 
the Duesseldorf house of Trust Agency chief Detlev Karsten 
Rohwedder, who was murdered in 1991. The security authorities 
are convinced that there is an international aspect to the 
attack on the CDU office: The "militant leftist autonomous 
group" (that is, according to the letter claiming responsibility 
for the attack) apparently wanted to demonstrate to foreign 
groups that someone is putting up resistance to an imperialist 
policy in the Third World. According to the analysis, the CDU, 
as a government party, will continue to be threatened by attacks 
on a "decentralist basis." 

</TEXT>

