<F P=100> ITALY &amp; VATICAN CITY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Vatican Establishes Relations With Israel </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Vatican Establishes Relations With Israel </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1506084794 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 0812 GMT 
15 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1506084794 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Televideo Teletext </F>
<F P=105>  Italian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Israel and the Vatican have established full 
diplomatic relations and have appointed the first papal nuncio 
and ambassador. Their names will be released after approval by 
both countries. This was announced by the Israeli Deputy Foreign 
Minister Yossi Beilin. 
  On 30 December 1993, the two sides signed a "fundamental 
agreement" that normalized Israeli-Vatican relations and opened 
the way to the establishing full diplomatic relations within six 
months. 

</TEXT>

