<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Demands Upgrade of Dialogue </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Demands Upgrade of Dialogue </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1406203394 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1900 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1406203394 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Cyprus Government demands an upgrading of the 
political dialogue on the Cyprus issue and an upgrading of the 
support given the UN secretary general by the Security Council 
in the efforts to solve the issue. This is the message conveyed 
by Foreign Minister Alekos Mikhailidhis during his contacts with 
the permanent members of the UN Security Council. Mikhailidhis, 
who has been in New York since yesterday, is expected to 
conclude his contacts with all members of the UN Security 
Council tonight. 
  In a statement to CyBC [Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation], 
Mikhailidhis stressed that he feels there is serious thought 
that the UN Security Council is showing strong signs of fatigue 
on the Cyprus issue. Mikhailidhis added that in order to 
overcome Turkish intransigence, specific directives should be 
issued to engage the Security Council and an agenda should be 
drawn up on the basis of which Security Council members will 
move on the direction of the Turkish side. 
  This evening, Mikhailidhis will attend a working dinner with 
UN official Marrack Goulding. Tomorrow, the foreign minister 
will go to Washington where he will meet with U.S. Deputy 
Secretary of State Strobe Talbott. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

