<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Denktas Cavils EU Observer; Meets With Feissel </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Denktas Cavils EU Observer; Meets With Feissel </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1406180994 Nicosia Bayrak Radio in Turkish 1530 GMT 14 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1406180994 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Bayrak Radio </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President Rauf Denktas has said that Serge Abou, 
whom the European Union [EU] assigned to be its Cyprus observer, 
has adopted a one-sided attitude and is making utterly pro-Greek 
Cypriot statements. 
  After his meeting with Gustave Feissel today, President 
Denktas commented on the statement by Abou in connection with 
the implementation of the confidence-building measures. Denktas 
said that it is unacceptable that Abou, an observer, should be a 
party to the issue or that he should try to mislead the EU. 
Denktas said that the latest statement by Abou shows how 
justified the Turkish Cypriots were in refusing to meet with 
him. Denktas said: Influenced by the Greek Cypriots, Abou is 
becoming a party to the issue and trying to influence the EU in 
favor of the Greek Cypriots. This is a regrettable development. 
In fact, it was a mistake to appoint this person. 
  Denktas concluded by saying that Abou was appointed probably 
as a reinforcement to the Greek-Cypriot side. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-43272 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drweu115_o_94008" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-WEU-94-115 </AU>
