<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Iranian Interior Minister Denies PKK in Iran </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Iranian Interior Minister Denies PKK in Iran </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1406155894 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1520 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA1406155894 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, June 14 (A.A.) -- Interior Minister Nahit 
Mentese on Tuesday [14 June] said that Turkey will not allow any 
activities against Iran within its territories. 
  Iranian Interior Minister 'Ali Mohammad Besharati-Jahromi, 
who is currently in Ankara on an official visit, said that 
Iran's borders are closed to the enemies of Turkey. 
  Besharati-Jahromi, who is continuing his contacts, in the 
afternoon visited Mentese at his office. 
  Mentese told reporters that Besharati on Monday met with 
President Suleyman Demirel, Prime Minister Tansu Ciller and 
Foreign Minister Hikmet Cetin and the meetings were held in a 
positive atmosphere. 
  As for Besharati-Jahromi, he said that relations with Turkey 
are developing day by day, especially in cultural and security 
fields. 
  He said that Iran was helpful to Turkey in combatting drug 
trafficking, especially those smuggled through its borders, 
adding that Iran's borders are closed to the enemies of Turkey. 
  `I can assure you that there are no PKK [Workers Party of 
Kurdistan] members in Iran,' Besharati-Jahromi said. 

</TEXT>

